Summary:
- Primary programming language: Java
- Primary web backend framework/stack: JAX-RS REST API implemented with RESTEasy on top of Netty (resteasy-netty4), i.e., a RESTful service built with JAX-RS and Netty

Reasoning and evidence:
- The repository contains a Maven project (pom.xml) with a Java-focused configuration (maven-compiler-plugin set to source/target 1.8).
- Dependencies include:
  - resteasy-netty4 and resteasy-jackson2-provider, which are RESTEasy components for building JAX-RS services on Netty.
  - javax.ws.rs-api (Jakarta/JSR-311 style API) indicating a JAX-RS-based service.
- The source tree (src/main/java) shows packages like com.datastax.mgmtapi and many REST resource classes under com.datastax.mgmtapi.resources and com.datastax.mgmtapi.resources.v1, which is typical for a RESTful API server.
- Netty-based server classes exist in the project (e.g., NettyJaxrsIPCServer.java, NettyJaxrsTLSServer.java), indicating Netty is used as the underlying server.
- The build also configures a shade plugin with a mainClass of com.datastax.mgmtapi.Cli, pointing to an executable Java application entry point, typical for a standalone server/CLI that launches the REST API.
- OpenAPI/Swagger integration is present (swagger-maven-plugin), which is common for REST APIs.

Conclusion:
This is a Java-based backend using a REST API built with JAX-RS (RESTEasy) on Netty. The project is Maven-driven and produces an executable jar with a main class at com.datastax.mgmtapi.Cli. The codebase includes numerous REST resources under src/main/java/com/datastax/mgmtapi.resources and Netty-based server classes, confirming the REST/Netty stack.
